This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it explores Deep Reinforcement Learning and proposes a new architecture and methods for training in parameterized action space. It also involves the use of state-of-the-art algorithms such as Trust Region Policy Optimization (TRPO) and Stochastic Value Gradient (SVG), which are commonly used in machine learning research. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) categories as it involves the application of reinforcement learning in various domains and proposes new methods for training in these domains.
